 What is the purpose of nodemon in a Node.js application?
‚úÖ Answer: nodemon automatically restarts the Node.js application when file changes are detected. It helps in development by removing the need to manually restart the server.

Example:

sh
Copy
Edit
nodemon server.js
2Ô∏è‚É£ Which command is used to install nodemon globally?
‚úÖ Answer:

sh
Copy
Edit
npm install -g nodemon
This installs nodemon globally so it can be used in any project.

3Ô∏è‚É£ What is the role of the package.json file in a Node.js project?
‚úÖ Answer: It stores metadata about the project, including dependencies, scripts, version, and configurations.

4Ô∏è‚É£ Which section of package.json is used to specify the scripts to run commands?
‚úÖ Answer: "scripts" section

Example in package.json:

json
Copy
Edit
"scripts": {
  "start": "node server.js",
  "dev": "nodemon server.js"
}
Run with:

npm run start
5Ô∏è‚É£ How do you install a package as a regular dependency (normal dependency)?
‚úÖ Answer:

sh
Copy
Edit
npm install package-name
This installs the package under the "dependencies" section.

6Ô∏è‚É£ What is the difference between "dependencies" and "devDependencies" in package.json?
‚úÖ Answer:

"dependencies" ‚Üí Required in both development & production

"devDependencies" ‚Üí Needed only in development (e.g., nodemon, jest)

7Ô∏è‚É£ Which of the following is true when you run npm install --production?
‚úÖ Answer: Only "dependencies" will be installed. "devDependencies" are skipped.

8Ô∏è‚É£ Which command is used to install a package as a dev dependency?
‚úÖ Answer:

sh
Copy
Edit
npm install package-name --save-dev
This adds the package to "devDependencies" in package.json.

9Ô∏è‚É£ What command would you use to uninstall a package using npm?
‚úÖ Answer:

sh
Copy
Edit
npm uninstall package-name
This removes the package from node_modules and package.json.

üîü Which of the following is NOT a default field created in package.json when running npm init?
‚úÖ Answer: The default fields are:

